According to tradition, it was founded in the late Heian period ({{ill|1069|ja|1069th year|12=draft|12=draft}}) by the decree of {{ill|Emperor Go-Sanjō|ja|後三条天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, upon the petition of {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshiie|ja|源義家|12=draft|12=draft}}, who brought a divided spirit of {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachimangū|ja|石清水八幡宮|12=draft|12=draft}}. During the {{ill|Sengoku period|ja|戦国時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, it fell into decline due to war, but was restored by {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|12=draft|12=draft}} when he became the lord of {{ill|Nagahama Castle (Ōmi Province)|ja|長浜城|12=draft|12=draft}}.

Since the Heian period, the temple {{ill|Shinhōjū-ji|ja|新放生寺|12=draft|12=draft}} existed within the grounds as the temple attached to the shrine, but it was abolished during the early Meiji period under the {{ill|Shinbutsu Bunri|ja|神仏分離|12=draft|12=draft}} decree, and all statues and documents were transferred to its remaining sub-temple, {{ill|Shana-in|ja|舎那院|12=draft|12=draft}}.

== Deities ==
* East Hall - {{ill|Emperor Chūai|ja|足仲彦尊|12=draft|12=draft}}
* Middle Hall - {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|誉田別尊|12=draft|12=draft}}
* West Hall - {{ill|Empress Jingū|ja|息長足姫尊|12=draft|12=draft}}

== Grounds ==
* Worship hall
* Main hall
* Auxiliary shrine: Kōra Shrine
* Auxiliary shrine: {{ill|Tsukubusuma Shrine|ja|都久夫須麻神社|12=draft|12=draft}}
* Auxiliary shrine: Tenmangū
* Auxiliary shrine: Konpiragū
* Subordinate shrine: Suehiro Inari Shrine
* Subordinate shrine: Jishu Shrine
* Subordinate shrine: Kumano Shrine
* Wish-fulfilling arrow

== Events and festivals ==
* {{ill|Hikiyama festival|ja|曳山祭|12=draft|12=draft}} – April 12-17. A traditional event dating back to the {{ill|Azuchi-Momoyama period|ja|安土桃山時代|12=draft|12=draft}}. One of the Three Great Float festivals of Japan.

== Access ==
* 13-minute walk from JR {{ill|Biwako Line|ja|琵琶湖線|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Nagahama Station|ja|長浜駅|12=draft|12=draft}}

