'''Nagahama Hachimangu''' (長浜八幡宮) is a [[Shinto shrine|shrine]] located in {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|ja|滋賀県}}, {{ill|Nagahama|ja|長浜市}}, Miyamae Town. It is a former {{ill|Prefectural shrine|ja|県社}} and is currently a {{ill|Beppyo shrines|ja|別表神社}}. It is famous for the {{ill|Nagahama Hikiyama festival|ja|長浜曳山祭}}, one of the {{ill|Three Great Float festivals of Japan|ja|日本三大一覧#祭り}}.

== History ==
According to tradition, it was founded in the late Heian period ({{ill|1069|ja|1069th year}}) by the decree of {{ill|Emperor Go-Sanjō|ja|後三条天皇}}, upon the petition of {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshiie|ja|源義家}}, who brought a divided spirit of {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachimangū|ja|石清水八幡宮}}. During the {{ill|Sengoku period|ja|戦国時代}}, it fell into decline due to war, but was restored by {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi}} when he became the lord of {{ill|Nagahama Castle (Ōmi Province)|ja|長浜城}}.

Since the Heian period, the temple {{ill|Shinhōjū-ji|ja|新放生寺}} existed within the grounds as the temple attached to the shrine, but it was abolished during the early Meiji period under the {{ill|Shinbutsu Bunri|ja|神仏分離}} decree, and all statues and documents were transferred to its remaining sub-temple, {{ill|Shana-in|ja|舎那院}}.

== Deities ==
* East Hall - {{ill|Emperor Chūai|ja|足仲彦尊}}
* Middle Hall - {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|誉田別尊}}
